title: Multiple cdist calls to counteract a memory error
body:
To counteract the memory error mentioned in Issue #80 , several cdist calls have been created.
The input data here is divided into pieces à 200 rows, which is a rather random number which I found worked for me, although I think a formula could be developed to determine how small those parts need to be depending on the size of the input data, the dimension the map should have and the available RAM.

title: adding get_bmus() to retrieve bmus from activation map
body:
Adding new method to retrieve bmus from an activation map.

For example : 

```python
am = som.get_surface_state(data)   # get activation map on some new data
bmus = som.get_bmus(am)            # -> get BMUs for this activation map
# on training data, this is equivalent to self.bmus
assert np.array_equal(som.bmus, som.get_bmus(som.get_surface_state()))
```
